<head>
<title>OneWorld Films</title>
</head>

<body bgcolor="#000000" text="#b2aab3" link="#ffffff" alink="#C0C0C0" vlink="#C0C0C0">


<BASE TARGET="_parent">

<FONT SIZE="+0">

<a name="_parent">
<center>
<br><h3>films on one world themes</h3>
<p>

<p>
</center> <b>Saigon Baby</b> is a complex adventure thriller about one couple's desperate attempt to adopt a baby in the Far East, aided by ex-pat middleman Jack. Michael and Kate's fraught journey forces them to confront the moral complexities of intercountry adoption, pitching the pain of childlessness against the realities of the international baby trade and prostitution in the developing world.<p>

<b>A BBC Film starring Kerry Fox, Douglas Hodge and John Hurt.<p>

<ul>
 Writer/ researcher - Guy Hibbert<br>
 Director - David Attwood<br>
 Producer - Jack Golding
</ul><p>


 The drama has been developed in association with <a href="../ibt/index.html">the International Broadcasting Trust (IBT)</a>, a London-based educational charity promoting global issues through television.<p></b>
<br clear=all>
</ul>

</center>



