<a name="_parent">
<center><br>

<h3>television programmes on one world themes</h3>
</center>

<h2> <a href="../tvandradio/tv_current.html">This Week's TV</h2></a>

Each week we bring you the best of UK and BBC World Service television on one world issues.  Programmes are listed day-by-day so that you never need miss that crucial screening. <p>


<b>THIS WEEK'S HIGHLIGHT:<br>
Saturday 9th October, C4, 11.40pm</b><br>
<b>Fascism</b><br> 
<ul><i>Purity</i> - <b>Jovan Dulovic</b>, crime reporter for the Serbian paper <i>Vremie</i>, has been covering the trial of the Yellow Wasps, a Serbian paramilitary group accused of being involved in the "ethnic cleansing" of 40,000 muslims. Dulovic has one fundamental question - how is it possible that the spectre of fascist genocide has returned to Europe so soon? </ul><p>



<center>
<p></center>

<h2> Past Television</h2>

An invaluable database of past television programmes shown in the UK and on BBC World Service.  Select the time period you want, and use the 'Find' command on your browser to search by topic or keyword.<p>
<i>These files are large - be warned!</i><br>
<b>
<a href="../tvandradio/tvpast_jan96.html">January 1996 - present</a><br>
<a href="../tvandradio/tvpast_july.html">1995 June - December 1995</a><br>
<a href="../tvandradio/tvpast_jantext.html">1995 Jan-June</a><br>
<a href="../cafod/cafod_progs.html">1982-1994 televison database</a><br>
<a href="../tvandradio/tvpast_jantext.html">1995 Jan - June (text only)</a><br></b>
<p align=center>

<p>

 <h2> Special Features</h2>
Major television highlights have been made into Special TV Features - with storyboards, summaries and video clips to download.<p>


<br><b><li type=square><a href="../tve/earth_report/index.html">BBC World: Earth Report</a></b><p>
A series of environmental slots, produced for BBC World Television by TVE, in co-operation with Carlton TV and WWF.  The programmes are presented by Sir David Attenborough, and aim to give a wide-ranging update on the state of the Earth. <br clear=left>
<p>

<ul>
 <br><b><li type=square><a href="../tvandradio/ophuls.html">The Troubles We've Seen</a></b><p>

Renowned French film Director Marcel Ophuls' 4-hour epic study of war correspondents at work in Sarajevo.  Is truth always the first casualty of war?<br><br clear=right><p>
<br>
</ul>
<br><b><li type=square><a href="../medmedia/ashrawi.html">Hanan Ashrawi</a></b><p>
A 50 minute documentary on the former PLO spokeswoman Hanan Ashrawi made by Palestinian Director Mai Masri as part of <a href="../tve/index.html">TVE's</a> 'Developing Stories'.<br clear=left>
<p>
<ul>
 <br>
<b><li type=square><a href="../owbt/drilling_video.html">The Drilling Fields</a></b><br>
Full transcript and video stills of the award winning documentary about the Ogoni people's battle with Shell, first shown in 1992.  

<ul><li><b><a href="../news/africa/nigeria.html">News reports on Nigeria</a></b><br clear=right>
<p></ul>

</ul>

