<br><br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../tvandradio/ophuls.mov">War Correspondent: the troubles we've seen</a></font><br></b>

Clip from Marcel Ophuls' epic study of war correspondents at work during the seige of Sarajevo.  Made during 1993, the film includes interviews with the BBC's John Simpson, John Burns from the New York Times and Stephane Manier from FR2. (1.2MB)<br><br>

<b>Also available: <a href="../tvandradio/ophuls.html">Storyboard of the film</a></b>

<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>




<br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../scf/scf_movs/scf1.mov">Case study from landmine victim in Cambodia</a></font><br></b>
Save the Children aid workers in Cambodia found ten- year-old Yung Chyeng just a week after a land-mine
accident which blew up his left leg.<p>

<b><font size=+1><a href="../scf/scf_movs/scf2.mov">Economic Impact of Landmine Injuries to families and Communities</a></font><br></b>
Mining land prevents communities from cultivating it, leading to malnutrition and even famine.  In the longer term, they prevent reconstruction work such as road projects and irrigation schemes.<p>

<b><font size=+1><a href="../scf/scf_movs/scf3.mov">Demining and Land-Mining Awareness Education</a></font><br></b>
Demining is a painfully slow process - it may take a team of 40 mine-clearers a week to cover an area the size of a football pitch.<br clear=left><br>
</center>


<ul><br><br><b><li><a href="../landmines/landmine_top.html">Special Feature on Landmines</a></b></ul>


<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>

<a href="../pwblf/index.html"></a>
<br><br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../pwblf/pwblf_pix/speech.mov">Prince of Wales Business Leaders Forum</a></font><br></b>

The Prince of Wales talks about the challenge facing international business leaders - to form a commitment to "good corporate citizenship".

<br clear=left><br><br clear=all><br>


<br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../news/newsflash_pix/boarding.mov"><a href="http://www.oneworld.org/misc/saynon/index.html">Say Non: "The Day of the Jacques"</a></font><br></b>
View the controversial "Say Non" video, a 30-second commercial broadcast in cinemas and on French television, which urges a boycott of French wine as a response to nuclear testing.

<br clear=left><br><br clear=all><br>

<br><br><br>

<b><font size=+1><a href="../news/newsflash_pix/boarding.mov">Greenpeace: The storming of the Rainbow Warrior</a></font><br></b>
Dramatic video footage of the French soldiers boarding the Rainbow Warrior during Greenpeace's opposition campaign to nuclear testing on Moruroa. (0.9MB)

<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>




<b><font size=+1><a href="../medmedia/gaza.mov">Medmedia: Women of Gaza</a></font><br></b>
"We were warned that most women would be afraid to speak about their lives in front of the camera," relates the Director of this MedMedia co-production.  "But we were struck by how openly and intimately they were prepared to speak." (1.6MB)<p>

<b><font size=+1><a href="../medmedia/medman.mov">Medmedia: Man on the Move</a></font><br></b>
Travelling on a Danish train, a young boy sits opposite a mysterious stranger who turns out to be 100,000 years old...  This is a story of human migrations, and the irresistible economic and climactic forces that have fuelled these migrations over the millenia. (1.1MB)



<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>



<br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../beijing/tvefaces.mov">A Woman's Place: Short Stories</a></font><br><br></b>
An introduction to TVE's selection of films to coincide and raise awareness of the Beijing Women's Conference.</a><br><br clear=all><br clear=all><br>

<a href="../com_fnd/index.html"></a><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../com_fnd/comm_pix/poverty.mov">Commonwealth Foundation: Paths Out of Poverty -The Role of NGOs</a></font><br><br></b>
A clip from a video produced by the Commonwealth Foundation. It features examples of successful NGO projects in several Commonwealth countries - including Pakistan, Bangladesh, Zimbabwe and the UK.  
<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>


<br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../media/camppan.mov">UNICEF: A Rwandan Refugee Camp</a></font><br><br></b>
Panoramic view of a refugee camp following the genocide in Rwanda.  At the time as many as 200,000 people were living in the Kibeho and Ndago camps - most still remain today.<p>


<font size=+1><a href="../ni/rwandaboy.mov">UNICEF: Rwandan Boy Accused of Genocide</a></font><br><br>


This video clip was filmed in a prison in Rwanda.  "They say I have killed somebody, but I haven't killed anybody," he says.<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>

<b><font size=+1><a href="../media_natura/pix/bema_monkeys.mov">Media Natura: Animal Detectives - Monkeys</a></font><br></b>
Video clip from the winner of the NPI Award for Best National Documentary and Current Affairs, in the Media Natura BEMA awards.  Subject: the use of monkeys in laboratories.  A Goldhawk Production in Association with Eco Detectives for Carlton TV.<p>

<br clear=all><br><br clear=all><br>



<br><br><br>
<b><font size=+1><a href="../medmedia/ashwari.mov">MedMedia: Hanan Ashwari - A Woman of her Time</a></font><br></b>
A clip from the 50-minute documentary about the former PLO spokeswoman, made by Palestinian Director Mai Masri for TVE's Developing Stories. (1.1MB) 




