<head>
<title>This Week's radio in the UK</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor=#ffffff>

<center>[RADIO]</center>
<br>

<center><h3>current UK radio programmes on one world themes: <br>September 26th - October 4th<p>
<li> <a href="../media/radio/listings/index.html">Radio listings for international services are now available</a></h3></center>

<br><p>

Use these buttons to jump to a specific day, or simply scroll
downhill.<p>
<ul><b>
<li><a href="#thu1">Thursday 26th September</a>
<li><a href="#fri1">Friday 27th September</a>
<li><a href="#sat">Saturday 28st September</a>
<li><a href="#sun">Sunday 29th September</a>
<li><a href="#mon">Monday 30th September</a>
<li><a href="#tue">Tuesday 1st October</a>
<li><a href="#wed">Wednesday 2nd October</a>
<li><a href="#thu">Thursday 3rd October</a>
<li><a href="#fri">Friday 4th October</a>
</b></ul><p><br>






<font size=2><b>Radio Frequencies:</b><br>
Radio 4 (R4) - FM 92.4-94.6, LW 198<br>
Radio 5 (R5) - MW 693, 909<br>
</font><p>
This information is provided by the <b><a href="../owbt/index.html">OneWorld Broadcasting Trust</a></b>
<p>




<a name="thu"></a><h3>THURSDAY 26th SEPTEMBER</h3>

<li><h3>How Common is Our Ground - R4,9.30am</h3>
<ul><b>Kate Ashbrook</b> chairwoman of the Rambler's Association discusses walkers' rights with <b>Martin Gillibrand</b> of the Moorland Association.</ul><p>


<li><h3>From Our Own Correspondent - R4, 11.30am</h3>
<ul>Colourful analysis from BBC correspondents around the world.</ul><p>

<li><h3>Can't You Take a Joke? - R4, 7.20pm</h3>
<ul><i>Women in the Police</i> - <b>Janet Cohen</b> asks why so few sexual harassment claims from women police officers are brought to bear as formal cases.</ul><p>


<li><h3>20/20 A View of the Century - R4, 8pm</h3>
<ul><i>Loving</i> - The twentieth century has seen the liberation of passion, both in public and in private.</ul><p>


<a name="fri"></a><h3>FRIDAY 27th SEPTEMBER</h3>

<ul><i>No OneWorld programmes today</i></ul><p>






<a name="sat"></a><h3>SATURDAY 28th SEPTEMBER</h3>
 

<li><h3>Global Concerns - World Service, 06.45 GMT</h3>
<ul>Weekly update on environmental issues.</ul><p>


<li><h3>Agenda - R4, 11am</h3>
<ul><i>The Warming of Britain</i> - How willing is the nation to cut down on greenhouse emissions?</ul><p>



<br>

<a name="sun"></a><h3>SUNDAY 29th SEPTEMBER</h3>



<li><h3>Development '96 - World Service, 06.15 GMT </h3>
<ul>From grassroot initiatives to government strategies, global villages to
village politics, <i>Development &nbsp;</i> offers listeners' reports,
interviews and dispatches from around the world.
</ul><p>

<li><h3>Michael Palin - R4, 8.50am</h3>
<ul><i>Week's Good Cause</i> - <b>Michael Palin</b> speaks up for a charity that is promoting alternatives to prison.</ul><p>


<li><h3>Global Concerns - World Sevice, 18.30GMT</h3>
<ul>Repeat of the current affairs programme that focuses on environmental issues.</ul><p>

<li><h3>The Spirit of America - R4, 11.45pm</h3>
<ul><i>The McCarthy Years</i> - In an interview with <b>Caryl Phillips</b>, journalist <b>Paul Robeson</b> talks about the  link between rascism in the US and Joe McCarthy's almost obsessive desire to expose communism.</ul><p>



<br>

<a name="mon"></a><h3>MONDAY 30th SEPTEMBER</h3>



<li><h3>Development '96 - World Service, 00.30 GMT </h3>
<ul>From grassroot initiatives to government strategies, global villages to
village politics, <i>Development &nbsp;</i> offers listeners reports,
interviews and dispatches from around the world.
</ul><p>

<li><h3>The Ecological Fightback in Latin America - World Service, 08.15GMT </h3>
<ul>Latin America faces an acute environmental crisis.  This programme looks at how people are making great efforts to change things for the better.
</ul><p>



<a name="tue"></a><h3>TUESDAY 1st OCTOBER</h3>

<li><h3>Global Concerns - World Service, 00.30 GMT</h3>
<ul>Weekly update on environmental issues.</ul><p>

<li><h3>Environment News - R5, 11am</h3><p>



<li><h3>All in the Mind - R4, 11.30am</h3>
<ul>Are citizens' juries an appropriate forum for the discussion of mental health problems? </ul><p>








<br>

<a name="wed"></a><h3>WEDNESDAY 2nd OCTOBER</h3>


<li><h3>Face the Facts - R4, 7.20pm</h3>
<ul>A team of investigators follow up on complaints from members of the public about injustice on a number of levels.</ul>

<br>

<a name="thu"></a><h3>THURSDAY 3rd OCTOBER</h3>


<li><h3>From Our Own Correspondent - R4, 11.30am</h3>
<ul>Colourful analysis from BBC correspondents around the world.</ul><p>


<li><h3>20/20 A View of the Century - R4, 8pm</h3>
<ul><i>Talking</i> - <b>John Tusa</b> asks how much weight one person's word can carry when placed against the might of modern communications.</ul><p>


<a name="fri"></a><h3>FRIDAY 4th OCTOBER</h3>

<ul><i>No OneWorld programmes today</i></ul><p>







<br>



<a href="tv_current.html"></a><br><br>

