<a name="cdrom"><p>


<center><br>
<h3>CD-Roms on sustainable development and human rights issues</h3>
<p></center>


<p><h2> 
<a href="../actionaid/actionaid_cdrom1.html">ACTIONAID's 'Discover India'</a></h2> <i> The opportunity to explore and discover, for yourself, the reality of life in India</i>
<p>
Drawing on over 20 years experience of working with poor communities in India and throughout the world, <a href="../actionaid/actionaid_pix/index.html">ACTIONAID</a> is ideally placed to provide real insights into life on the sub-continent.
<p><br clear=all><br><br>
<p>
<center><p></center>
<h2> <a href="../amnesty/amnesty_pix/amnesty_rights.html">Amnesty Interactive Human Rights Education</a></h2>
<p>
<a href="../amnesty/index.html">Amnesty International</a> brings its human rights message to the home and classroom on a multimedia CD-ROM, featuring stories, pictures, musical video, and animation from around the world.
<br clear=left>
<p>

<p>
<center><p></center>
<h2> <a href="../tvandradio/ngo_cdrom.html">NGO's Earth Summit</h2> </a><p>
<ul>The first and unique compilation of  NGO 
documents  on the United Nations Conference  on  Environment 
and Development.</ul><p>
<p>
<center><p></center>
<h2>
 <a href="../tvandradio/atlas_cdrom.html">Electronic Arts' 3D-Atlas</h2></a><p>
<b><i>The Earth's not flat. Why should your atlas be?</i></b><br>
<b>Electonic Arts 3D Atlas</b> is a revolutionary CD-ROM which breaks away from the conventions of distorted flat maps to show the world how it really is - a globe. This 3D globe, created entirely from satellite images, can be rotated in any direction with a simple click of the mouse, and can be zoomed to nine levels. Cities, mountains, country borders and other geographical features can be easily overlaid.<p>

