<HEAD>
<TITLE>Knowing about this Convention</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=FFFFFF>
<CENTER>
<H1><FONT COLOR=BLUE>Knowing about this Convention</FONT></H1><BR>
<P>
<IMG SRC="../unicef_pix/know.gif"><BR>
<P>
</CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=4><B>This is one of the most important rights to know
about this Convention.</B><BR>
<P>
<DL>
<DT>Article 42
<DD>All adults and all children should know about this Convention.
You have a right to learn about your rights and adults should learn
about them too.
<P>
</DL>
You might want to read <A
HREF="http://www.unicef.org/crc/conven.htm">more</A> about the
Convention.<BR>
<P>
Talk about it with your friends, your parents and your teachers. By
telling other people about children's rights, you will be helping
other children too. The more people understand that children have
rights, the more likely they are to help everyone get what they need
to grow up healthy, and safe, and free.<BR>
<P>
<B>If you are not sure what any of your rights mean, why not <A
HREF="mailto:info@unicef.demon.co.uk">write</A> to us and ask?<BR>
<P>
We'll do our best to answer your questions!</B><BR>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<A HREF="rights.html"><IMG border=0 SRC="../unicef_pix/know.gif"
ALIGN=LEFT></A>Return to <A HREF="rights.html">Know Your Rights</A>
Home Page.</FONT>
