<head>
<title>VSO PRESS RELEASE International Volunteer Day </title>
<!!keys:VSO>
</head>
<body>
 [ VSO Books ] <br>

<br clear=all>
<i>The material that follows has been provided by &nbsp;</i><a href="vso_info.html"> Voluntary Service Overseas</a>
<hr>
<p>

<center><h2>PRESS RELEASE</h2>
<h1>International Volunteer Day </h1>

<h3>5 December 1995</h3></center>


<b>VSO, </b>the development aid charity, will be celebrating <b>International Volunteer Day </b>on December 5 by highlighting VSO Volunteers working towards <b>peace and reconstruction.</b><p>


Long after the <b>media spotlight </b>has moved on, and often after emergency relief charities have left, VSO has volunteers working in more than 50 of the world's poorest countries to help build the peace after the ravages of war and bitter conflict.<p>


Generations of children in countries like <b>Cambodia </b>and <b>Namibia </b>have never learnt anything but how to fight and survive. VSO Volunteers are there now, retraining fighters to become mechanics for tractors and lorries, teaching former refugees new skills and languages and fitting artificial limbs to farmers hit by anti-personnel mines so they can continue working.<p>


Volunteers in countries like <b>South Africa, Vietnam </b>and <b>Eritrea </b>are living with communities devastated by years of war. Rebuilding schools, repairing roads and giving hope, VSO Volunteers are helping the world's poorest people to reconstruct their lives. By economic regeneration, skills retraining and social integration through sport and music, local people are winning the struggle against the debilitating effects of prolonged conflict. <p>


VSO Volunteers work in partnership with local people for two years. When they leave their skills remain behind helping the community towards a brighter future for generations to come.<p>


If you want more information about volunteering with <b>Voluntary Service Overseas </b>and help make a difference in the developing world, call <b>0181 780 1331 </b>now.<p>


<a href="cases.html">Case Studies of VSO Volunteers working in Peace and Reconstruction </a><br>
More information about four volunteers working in peace and reconstruction in four different parts of the world.<p>



For further information about Local Groups and Returned Volunteers from your area please contact<br>
<b>Betty McBride, Lara Date </b>or <b>Simon Watts </b>- VSO Press Office (London) <br>
0181 780 2266 - <i>Switchboard </i><br>			
0181 780 1349 - <i>direct line </i><br>
0181 780 9283 - <i>direct fax </i><p><hr><p>


©Copyright: Voluntary Service Overseas 1995
<hr>
<a href="index.html"> VSO Home Page</a>
<hr>
</body>
</html>
