<h2> INFORMATION PAGE</h2>
<i>The material that follows has been provided by CAFOD</i>

<hr>
<p>
<h2>CAFOD is...</h2>
<p>
CAFOD is one of the UK's major relief and development agencies. Established in 1962 by the Catholic Bishops' Conference, it is the Catholic aid agency for England and Wales. It works overseas through local partners. Its aim is to promote human development and social justice in witness to Christian faith and gospel values. 
<p>
CAFOD supports over 1,000 development projects in 75 countries in Africa, Asia, the Pacific, Latin America, the Caribbean, and Eastern Europe including: 
<p>
<ul><li>food production and agriculture<br>
<li>water development and irrigation<br>
<li>preventive health care<br>
<li>leadership and skills training, especially among refugees<br>
<li>adult education and literacy programmes<br>
<li>AIDS control and prevention</ul>
<p>
Development projects supported by CAFOD aim to help people help themselves, without regard to race, religion or politics. 
<p>
CAFOD's concern is with the causes as well as the effects of poverty and injustice. 
<p>
CAFOD also responds to emergencies worldwide, providing relief and rehabilitation assistance, often through its membership of the Church's network of relief agencies, Caritas Internationalis.
<p>
CAFOD also works to raise awareness at home of the causes of poverty and injustice in the developing world and the steps we can take here to bring about change. 
<p>
CAFOD's work is an expression of solidarity, of love, of our yearning for justice for the poor in the developing world.' Cardinal Basil Hume 
<p>
For further information about CAFOD's work, contact your local Regional Organiser: 
<p>
