<HTML><HEAD>    <TITLE>National Non-Uniform Day Acknowledgements</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><a href="nnud_contents.html"><img align=right hspace=10 src="unicef_pix/nnud_leaf.gif"></a><IMG SRC="unicef_pix/unicef_logo.gif" WIDTH="160" HEIGHT="53" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0" ALIGN=left><BR clear=all><br><HR><BR><P><CENTER><B>Data File - The cost of education<BR></B></CENTER><P><I>750/- (Tanzanian shillings) = &#163;1.00 (Sterling)</I><BR><BR>Gertrude and Rosalyne <a href="unicef_pix/nnud_8.jpg">(Picture 8)</a> goto Olympio School,  an English medium state school. Although there are no'fees' their education is not free. Lisbert, their younger sister goes toa nursery school. <BR><BR>This is the yearly cost of their education:<BR><H3>1. Olympio School</H3><BR>a) Uniform<BR>Skirts - 2 per child @ 5500/- (&#163;7.33) each<BR>Blouses - 2 each    @ 2500/- (3.33) each<BR>Black leather shoes - 1 pair each @ 12,000/- (&#163;16.00) per pair<BR>White socks - 2 pairs each @ 1,500/- (&#163;2.00)<BR><BR>b) Stationery<BR>Books, pens, pencils etc. - 10,000/- (&#163;13.33) for each child.<BR><BR>c) School Building Fund<BR>There is an annual charge for each child of 10,000/- (&#163;13.33).<BR><BR>d) Homework<BR>Teachers make a charge for setting and marking homework. Monthly cost ofhomework for each child is 8000/-(&#163;10.67).<BR><H3>2. The nursery school </H3><BR>Lisbert goes to a private nursery school.<BR><BR>a) Uniform<BR>Lisbert has two sets of uniform, each set costs 5000/- (&#163;6.67).<BR><BR>b) Stationery<BR>Books, pencils etc. 10,000/- (&#163;13.33).<BR><BR>c) Registration Fee<BR>One-off fee when Lisbert started at the school of 10,000/- (&#163;13.33).<BR><BR>d) School Fees<BR>Each term there are school fees of 105,000/- (&#163;140.00).<BR>There are three terms in the school year<BR><H3>Questions</H3><BR>All answers in: a) Tanzanian shillings (/-) b) Pounds sterling (&#163;)<BR><BR>1. What is the total cost to Gertrude, Rosalyne's and Lisbert's parentsper year for their children's school clothing? Give your answer as an itemisedbill.<BR><BR>2. What is the total cost per year of the stationery used by the childrenwho go to Olympio School?<BR><BR>3. What was the total cost of Lisbert's first year at the nursery school?<BR> 	<BR>4. School lasts for 9 months a year. How much does Gertrude's and Rosalyne'shomework cost per year?<BR><BR>5. What will the total cost be for all three children when Lisbert is inher second year at nursery school?<BR><H3>Cost of education for one child at an ordinary state primary school</H3><BR>4,000/- 'donation' to the school every year<BR>1,500/- for exercise books<BR>10,000/- for text books<BR>6,000/- for 2 sets of uniform<BR>60/- per day for bus fare<BR>200/- pocket money for snacks etc.<BR><BR>See if you can make up a set of questions using this information.<BR><BR><HR>&copy;Copyright: UNICEF 1996 <HR><a href="index.html" target="_parent"><IMG SRC="unicef_pix/unicef_logo2.gif"WIDTH="45" HEIGHT="36" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3" ALIGN=bottom>Unicef Home Page</A><HR></BODY></HTML>
