<html>
<head>
<title>Rwanda: Special Report - Background</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body link="#215e21" alink="#ooffoo" vlink="#4a766e">
<center><h1><font size=+4>B</font>OSNIA: <font size=+4>S</font>PECIAL <font size=+4>R</font>EPORT </h1></center>
 

<h1>How You Can Help</h1>



<li><a href="../oxfam/index.html">
<b>Oxfam</b></a> has had an office in Tuzla since 1993, and its work has
been predominantly with displaced women and children and disabled
people. It has an emergency contingency stock of clothing,
blankets and shoes.  Oxfam has begun a special appeal due to the worsening of the refugee crisis after the Serb takeover of Srebrenica</i></b><p>

<b>To make a donation, please call + 44 (0)1865 313131</b><p>

<hr align=left width=71%><p>


<li><b><a href="../unicef/index.html">Unicef</a>
</b> have launched an appeal to raise £1 million for the <a href="../unicef/unicef_bosnia_appeal.html">children of Bosnia.</a>  They need funds to provide clean water, food, blankets and medical supplies to help keep children alive.<p>
<b>To make a donation, please call:<br>
0345 312312 or +44 345 312312 (calls are charged at local rates within the UK) quoting Room number B6 or send donations to:<br>
Bosnian Children's Appeal, UNICEF, Room B6, FREEPOST, Chelmsford CM28BR, UK</b> <p>
<hr align=left width=71%><p>

<li><b><a href="../christian_aid/index.html">Christian Aid</a></b>  have launched an <a href="../christian_aid/caid_bosnia.html">appeal to aid the refugees in Tuzla.</a>  The funds raised will be used for their humanitarian work in many stricken parts of the former Yugoslavia.  To donate to their aid effort, call + 44 (0)171 620 4444</ul><p>
<hr align=left width=71%><p>


<li><b><a href="../cafod/index.html">CAFOD</a></b> also has an appeal line.  They can be reached on + 44 (0)171 733 7900<p>
<hr align=left width=71%><p>

<li><b><a href="../scf/index.html">Save the Children Fund's </a></b> Bosnia appeal line is + 44 (0)171 703 5400<p>


 <p>


