<center><h1><font size=+4>B</font>OSNIA: <font size=+4>S</font>PECIAL <font size=+4>R</font>EPORT </h1></center>


<p>

<h1>External Links</h2>
<h2>Links to other Internet sites focusing on Bosnia</h2>

<ul>
<li>The US Department of State has a <b><a href="http://dosfan.lib.uic.edu/boshome.html">home page on Bosnia</a></b>, featuring the texts and summary of the Dayton Agreement, daily State Dept Press Briefings, Fact Sheets and other information.<p>

<li>The <b><a href="http://www.cco.caltech.edu/~bosnia/bosnia.html">Bosnia homepage,</a></b> run from the California Institute of Technology, contains history, information on war criminals, and a gallery of photos from the conflict.<p>

<li>Further information on the former Yugoslavia is also on the Web courtesy of <b><a href="http://www.emse.fr/~maillot/HTML/PERSO/E/YUGO/">Jean-Luc Maillot</a></b>, whose site has material on human rights, multi-ethnism, the International Tribunal and reports from UN experts.  Well worth a visit.<p>

<li>You can also take a <b><a href="http://geog.gmu.edu/gess/jwc/bosnia/bosnia.html">virtual fieldtrip to Bosnia,</a></b> courtesy of Jeremy Crampton in the USA.<p>

<li>If you're interested in Croatian culture and politics <b><a href="http://www.hrnet.org/~napredak/">Napredak On-Line</a></b> is devoted to documenting the activities of the Bosnian Croat community.<p>

<li>The latest news is frequently posted to the newsgroup <b><a href="news:misc.news.bosnia">misc.news.bosnia</a></b><p>

<li>Other Usenet newsgroups on Bosnia include <b><a href="news:soc.culture.bosna-herzgvna">soc.culture.bosna-herzgvna</a></b> and <b><a href="news:alt.current-events.bosnia">alt.current-events.bosnia</a></b> - both of which contain some extremist views and strong opinions.

</b><p>
<li>The <b><a href="http://www.i3tele.com/photo_perspectives_museum/faces/faces.html">Faces of Sorrow</a></b> exhibition, offering "indisputable pictorial witness to the searing effects of man's inhumanity to mankind".<p>
<li>The <b><a href="http://www.blackstar.com/about/news/turnley/bosnia/bosnia1.html">Black Star exhibition</a></b> of Peter Turnley's photographs of Bosnian refugees.<p>
<li>The <b><a href="http://tux.music.asu.edu:80/~john/bosnia/Bosnia_Help_Page.html">Bosnia Help Page</a></b> a collection of humanitarian resources concerned with the former Yugoslavia.<p>
<li>For an alternative viewpoint, see the pro-Serb <b><a href="http://www.umiacs.umd.edu/users/lpv/YU/HTML/yu.html">"Yugoslavia" pages.</a></b><p>

<center></ul><font size=-1><i>OneWorld Online can take no responsibility for what you find on external pages - so take care!</i></font></center><p>

 </ul>

<p>

