<head>
<title>NI UN reform - Dec 94</title>
<!!keys: New Internationalist+UN>
</head>
<body>
<h2>New Internationalist UN Reform Game</h2>
<hr>
<p>
<h3>A car bomb exploded right beside you.</h3>
<p>

<p>
Of course it's outrageous  these countries have a veto. But
there is a practical argument for it: the League of Nations
failed in the 1930s because powerful countries left rather than
be bound by its decisions. The veto immobilized the UN in the
Cold War years but it did at least keep both superpowers talking
to each other. 
<p>
<a href="NIreform6.html">Try again</a><p>
</body>
