<body>
<h2>New Internationalist UN Reform Game</h2>
<hr>
<p>
<h3>Pass on.</h3>
<p>
This would be a constructive
and useful change and it's just possible that in a climate
clamouring for reform the major powers would consent. At the
moment Britain follows Washington's direction so completely that
raising two votes against would be no problem. But circumstances
and governments change and the US could be isolated in the
future.
<p>


<p>
<h3>Congratulations!</h3>
<p>
You have navigated a successful reform of the
Security Council. But will these changes be enough to win the UN
new credibility in the world?
