<head>
<title> AZIONE AIUTO- ACTIONAID in Italy</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center> AZIONE AIUTO- ACTIONAID in Italy</h2>



<b><a href="../azione_aiuto/index.html" target="_parent">Premi qui per leggere il testo in
Italiano</a></b>
<p>


AZIONE AIUTO is the Italian branch of ACTIONAID. It supports long-term community development work in
Bolivia, <a href="ethiopia.html">Ethiopia</a>, <a href="ghana.html">Ghana</a>, <a
href="india.html">India</a>, <a href="malawi.html">Malawi</a>, <a href="mozamb.html">Mozambique</a>
and <a href="somali.html">Somaliland</a>.
<p>

The funds raised by the organisation are spent on vital work in education, health, water, food
security, community organisation and income generation. AZIONE AIUTO also aims to increase awareness
of the causes and effects of poverty in the developing world in Italy.
<p>

Fundraising activities are focused on providing a link between donors in Italy and the work they
support in the developing world. The principal mechanism is child sponsorship, where in return for an
annual subscription of Lit 480,000 sponsors are linked with a child in  a developing country. The
subscription pays for a range of services for the child, family and community to help them to a more
self-reliant future. The sponsor initially receives a case history of the child, updates three times
a year on the child's progress, how their subscriptions have been spent and what has been achieved.
<p>

In addition to child sponsorship, we offer the opportunity for individuals, groups and companies to
donate to projects not funded through child sponsorship, but as with the sponsorship scheme, priority
is placed on accountability to donors by offering reports on how money has been used and showing the
impact of these projects on the lives of the poor.
<p>


<b>For more information contact:<p>


AZIONE AIUTO, Via Trincea delle Frasche 2, 20136 Milan, Italy<p>


Tel: + (02) 835 6706 <br>				Fax: + (02) 835 6740</b>
<p><hr>
