<head>
<title> MALAWI</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<font face="arial, helvetica">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center>MALAWI</h2>
<p>
<img src="../pix/malawi.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=2 width=257 height=451 alt="Map of Malawi" align=left>

<hr>

<p><b>Key National Statistics</b>

<p>Population	11.2 million

<p>Population growth rate	2.3% a year

<p>Under-five child mortality	223
(deaths per 1,000 live births)

<p>Rural population with 	50%
access to safe water

<p>Adult literacy rate	53.9%

<p><hr>
<h3>Programme Overview </h3>

<p>ACTIONAID began work in Malawi in 1990 and is now, through programmes in two areas of the country,
reaching more than 80,000 people. In both areas the primary need is to increase agricultural
productivity and therefore people's capacity to provide enough food to subsist. 

<p>Food shortages are common between November and March each year and with limited access to clean
water and poor health care and education facilities, life is particularly hard for the rural poor.
<br clear=all>
<h3>Examples of ACTIONAID's work in Malawi:</h3>

<p><ul><li>an over-dependence on maize is increasing the vulnerability of farming families to
drought. ACTIONAID is providing seed credit and training in the cultivation of sweet potato and
cassava, which are drought resistant. Already more than 2,000 families have participated in the
programme.

<p><li>in 1995 the maize harvest failed and 60 per cent of households in Masakambewa stood to run out
of food by August, leaving them with an eight month food gap before the next harvest. ACTIONAID
helped by distributing seeds nation-wide to ensure farmers had enough to plant for the next season,
while a government-run programme supplied food to families to bridge the hungry months from August to
May.

<p><li>AIDS is a growing problem  - World Health Organisation estimates suggest that approximately 20
per cent of the sexually active population could be HIV positive. ACTIONAID is, through its
Strategies for Action project, supporting community-based HIV/AIDS groups working to combat and
alleviate the effects of the disease.
</ul></font>
<!--footer-->
<p><hr>
<p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img
src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="index.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li
type=square><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">Join
ACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="index.html">Country Programmes</a></b></font>
<br clear=all>
