<html>
<head>
<title> MOZAMBIQUE</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" link="#000066" vlink="#FF6600">
<font face="arial, helvetica">
<a href="../info/index.html"><img src="../pix/logo-t.gif" width=96 height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<h6 align=left>The material that follows has been provided by <a
href="../info/index.html">ACTIONAID</a></h6><br clear=right>
<br>

<h2 align=center> MOZAMBIQUE</h2>
<p align=center>
<img src="../pix/mozam.jpg" hspace=5 vspace=2 width=428 height=272 alt="Map of
Mozambique">
</p>
<hr>
<b>Key National Statistics</b>

<p>Population	16.7 million

<p>Population growth rate	3.2% a year

<p>Under-five child mortality	282
(deaths per 1,000 live births)

<p>Rural population with 	17%
access to safe water

<p>Adult literacy rate	37%	
<br clear=left>
<p><hr>
<h3>Programme Overview </h3>

<p>ACTIONAID began work in 1988 in the coastal districts of Zambezia province. The programme began as
a relief operation helping 200,000 displaced people who had fled their villages during Mozambique's
civil war
for the safety of Pebane and nearby islands. 

<p>With peace, ACTIONAID is now undertaking a full scale development programme in the area, aiming to
improve long-term food security to help rebuild roads, bridges and other infrastructure and to help
people
take charge of their own development. Work will also begin further south in Maputo, where ACTIONAID
will
help the poor rural communities improve food security, health awareness, literacy and to develop new
ways of generating income.

<h3>Examples of ACTIONAID's work in Mozambique:</h3>

<p><ul><li>ACTIONAID's Roads and Bridges Rehabilitation Unit is assisting the government's
infrastructure
programme with repairs to roads and bridges destroyed during the 16 years of civil war. One of its
first
achievements, the construction of four small bridges in Pebane, opened up trading for many farmers
who
are cut off for most of the year.

<p><li>The civil war devastated an education system that was already starved of funds. ACTIONAID is
helping to train teachers, provide equipment and rehabilitate school buildings. More than 20,000
children
have benefited from the improvements already.

<p><li>Now that many families have once again become self-sufficient following displacement during
the
war and the drought between 1989 and 1992, the need is to help farmers increase yields so that food
security and nutrition increases. To this end, ACTIONAID is training farmers in new techniques,
helping to
establish new water sources and has setting up a savings and credit scheme so that farmers can invest
in
much needed equipment or seed.
</ul>
</font>

<!--footer-->
<p><hr>
<p><a href="../home.html"><img src="../pix/home.gif" width=46
height=41 hspace=10
vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a><a href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent"><img
src="../pix/globe1.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a> <a href="index.html"><img src="../pix/back.gif" width=46
height=41
hspace=10 vspace=2 border=0 align=right></a>
<font size=1 face=helvetica, arial><b><li type=square><a href="../home.html">Home Page</a> <li
type=square><a
href="../fight/index.html" target="_parent">Join
ACTIONAID</a> <li type=square><a href="index.html">Country Programmes</a></b></font>
<br clear=all>
<p></body>
</html>
