<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<H2><IMG SRC  = "../images/euldc.gif"><p>
EU-LDC Trade and Capital Relations Network<br>EU-LDC News</h2>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:memedovic@NEI.NL">Dr. Olga Memedovic</a></center>
<p>
<hr><p>
The Newsletter reports on ongoing research, conferences and policy initiatives. Networkers are encouraged to use the Newsletter to: (i) express their opinion on topical issues; (ii) inform their fellow networkers of activities in which they participate; (iii) get a wider audience for their ideas and opinions; and (iv) to  distribute other information which might be of interest to their fellow networkers.
<p>
Since the inception of the Network 10 issues of EU-LDC News have been released. The NEI has received a great number of letters of support and requests for all so far published issues of the Newsletter, from policy makers and researchers from both LDCs and developed countries. To quote only a few:
<ul>
The publication EU-LDC News and the four issues of 1995, edited by you, will be of great value to our centre."
Trade information Service, Ministry of Foreign Trade Havana, Cuba.
<p>
"I believe my Ministry, myself and others will benefit a lot from your Institution (EU-LDC). ...we shall try to share this line of thinking and experiences in all its possible ways." Ogbe Abraha, Minister of Trade and Industry, State of Eritrea.
<p>
"I was delighted by the copy of EU-LDC News which I think is very useful and fills a yawning gap in the information flow profile between the EU and those of us in the non EU-countries." Tawia Akyea, Executive Secretary, Ghana Export Promotion Council, Ghana.
<p>
"We had the opportunity to review the third issue of your publication and find the topics discussed to be very relevant and useful to our work." Ministry of Agriculture, Trade and Industry, Energy and Production, Grenada.
<p>
"I have gone through the publication EU-LDC News and I must compliment you for taking this initiative of trying to bring the EU and LDCs nearer." Dr. S.P. Gupta, Director of Indian Council for Research on International Economic Relations, India.
<p>
"The EU-LDC News publication received by the Department was found to be most interesting and useful in its analysis of EU-LDC relations." The Director-General, Department of Foreign Affairs, Pretoria, Republic of South Africa.
<p>
"I believe the bulletin will help us and the other members of the staff to understand the socio-economic relations between the European Union countries and the less developed countries." Office of the Prime Minister and First Vice-president (Principal Secretary Tanzania), Tanzania.
<p>
"Your publication of EU-LDCs News is very interesting." Center for International Economics Director Dr. Suthiphand Chirathirat, Faculty of Economics Bangkok, Thailand.
<p>
"We  look forward  to contributing to future issues of your outstanding publication." Research Chief Division, African Development Bank, Ivory Coast.
</ul>
<p>
The 1996 September issue of EU-LDC News will deal with the trade and capital relations between EU and MERCUSOR. For the 1997 issues core subjects are defined such as: EU - Maghreb; European Monetary Union; Consequences for the EU-LDC Trade and Capital Relations; Private Capital Flows to LDCs - With Particular Emphasis on the Role of the EU; Access to EU Markets in the Post Uruguay Round Era; EU Policy Coherence, and Multilateralism versus Regionalism - What role for the EU?
<p>
